Both deliverables written and validated.

**Headline findings across 10 iterations:**

- **Dominant signal:** a three-way synergy `feature_014 × feature_027 × feature_035` (3-way interaction β=+2.20, p<10⁻²⁹). 7 of 8 cells in the 2×2×2 table show response rate 16-17%; the triple-positive cell (n=427) jumps to 62.1%.
- **Prognostic gradient:** `feature_057` (3-level ordinal) — response 21.3% → 15.5% → 11.2% across levels (OR 0.68/level, p≈10⁻⁹⁷).
- **Continuous prognostics (negative):** `feature_011` (p≈10⁻³⁹), `feature_006`, `feature_063`, `feature_092`. Positive: `feature_099`.
- **`feature_035` is a predictive biomarker** with modest main effect (+5 pp) that becomes large only when `feature_014` and `feature_027` are also present.
- **No demographic disparity after clinical adjustment.** Race shows a small unadjusted gap (white 17.3% vs black 15.7%, p=0.01) that vanishes (p>0.13) after adjusting for clinical predictors, primarily `feature_011`. Insurance, age, and `feature_007` show no association at any stage.

Files written: `transcript.json` (10 iterations, 26 hypotheses, 25 analyses, schema-validated) and `analysis_summary.txt`.
